you! <br>a geonid heeds the command and joins to form the Menhir. <br>a geonid shaman heeds the command and joins to form the Menhir. <br>a geonid heeds the command and joins to form the Menhir. <br>a geonid heeds the command and joins to form the Menhir. <br>a geonid heeds the command and joins to form the Menhir. <br>a geonid heeds the command and joins to form the Menhir. <br>a geonid shaman heeds the command and joins to form the Menhir. <br><br>The Menhir begins to cast a spell.<br>The Menhir begins to radiate.<br><br>The Menhir begins to cast a spell.<br>The Menhir's skin is slicked by a silvery glow.<br><br>The Menhir 's resonation becomes dangerously intense. Cracks form along the stones like lightning across a sky. Smaller stones begin to crumble and fall to the ground as the earth begins to tremor. Something seems to have gone wrong, you decide you should leave the immediate area as quickly as possible <br><br>The Menhir begins to cast a spell.<br>The Menhir begins to shudder violently. A terrifying screech rips through the air. For a split second you hear, from within your mind, the Geonids all cry out at once in fear and regret. The structure then whines as the stone grinds against one another in a last effort of defiance before exploding and showering the area in flame, crystal, and rock. The Menhir is destroyed. <br><br><br><br>The Menhir was red to me at 53 and blue to a lvl 60 Warrior that was there with me.  The Menhir lasted around 2 minutes total time and then exploded.  Afterwards I had thought that I could have possibly saved the Menhir by turning in the Focus item.  Well suffice to say, this was disproven by Fawyn an enchanter that also completed the quest two hours after I did.<br> <p>Ardoon Nazuul <BR>Lvl 52 Wizard<BR>Rodcet Nife<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udimuyensylvanesty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>